C(7) = \frac{7}{4} \sum_{y = 2}^4 \sum_{x = 1}^{y-1} \sum_{z=y+1}^6 1 = \frac{7}{4} \sum_{y = 2}^4 (y-1)(6-y) = 35
C(n) = \frac n 4 \sum\limits_{y=2}^{n-2} (y-1)(n-1-y)
C(n) = \frac 4 2 \sum\limits_{k=1}^{n-3} ((n-2)k - k^2)
\sum_{k=1}^N k = \frac{N(N+1)}2
\sum\limits_{k=1}^N k^2 = \frac{N(N+2)(2N+1)}{6}
C(n) = \frac{n}{4}\left((n-2)\frac{(n-3)(n-2))}{2}-\frac{(n-3)(n-2)(2n-5)}{6}\right)
C(n) = \frac{n(n-1)(n-2)(n-3)}{24}
